	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hail all,<BR>
   Just wanted to update the info concerning this quest.  At the time of this posting, I'm the one in the 2 pics... I completed this quest in about 6 hours, 2 hours of which were spent trying to get the one in LGuk.  <BR>
<BR>
Died once there as I was unfamiliar with the zone and, sad to say, ran into a gargoyle who didn't mind my IvU.  Finally found a high lvl Cleric to cast IvU and a friend in the hand room to give decent directions, ran in, waited for them to kill the hand, and tada, got the rod.<BR>
<BR>
Erud's crossing no longer has the sharks.  If you see sharks, you're in the wrong spot.  Check graffe.com for the coordinates of the rod, it's pretty tough to find, as there aren't any landmarks.<BR>
<BR>
Dagnor's cauldron... what can i say, get enduring breath and swim to the deepest part of the lake straight out from unrest and you'll find it.  I didn't see any mobs on the way down, but I was invis so it didn't matter.<BR>
<BR>
Oasis, invis worked like a charm, swam down, got the rod, back out again.<BR>
<BR>
Lake Rathetear, definately the scariest part, just start from the east side of the island and swim forever, you'll find the tower eventually.  Btw, water stones or enduring breath is a MUST.  I'd recommend getting a friendly mage to summon 2 water stones for this one.  Again, invised, swam in, nabbed it, swam out the other side, no problems at all.<BR>
<BR>
Neriak, bah, invis and run right to it, just get a map first, MUCH easier.<BR>
<BR>
Unrest, pretty hard to see, but it's under the ledge on the estate side of the little river.<BR>
<BR>
Everfrost, bit scary cause i didn't really know the way.  At lvl 24 the ice boned won't agro you any more, and even at 23 putting them down is cake.  WATCH OUT, after you pick up the rod, a quite large polar bear, conned very red at 23, spawns in the hall on the way out.  HAVE INVIS ON and you'll walk right past him.  Side note, water stones are a must here as well, it's a decent swim to get to the tunnels.<BR>
<BR>
Qeynos Catacombs shark pit, get a map, invis, no agro, you got another rod.<BR>
<BR>
Highpass Hold heh, just sitting in the bottom of the pool, np.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, that should clear up any misconceptions you may have.  By far, the LGuk run is the toughest.  If you've ever EVER killed any frogloks, forget this quest, as there are live froggies in LGuk as well.  I was lucky in that my froglok faction was good.  I can walk all the way to LGuk zone with no problems =)<BR>
<BR>
Good luck getting this staff, and please, at your next convenience, send in feedback for a new graphic.  It looks just like a water crystal staff (grrr).<BR>
<BR>
Goramon Coldfire &lt;Unbroken Circle of Valor&gt;<BR>
Erudite Wizard of 26 fizzles (as of last night anyway)<BR>
Vazaelle<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
